SUPPLIER ESCALATION — QUICK REFERENCE CARD
Agent: Supplier Escalation Assistant
Version: 2.0 | May 2026

HOW TO USE THIS AGENT:
1. Open Copilot Chat or Teams
2. Select "Supplier Escalation Agent" from the agent list
3. Describe the issue in plain language

EXAMPLE INPUTS:
- "Supplier X missed shipment for part Y, affects line Z starting Monday"
- "Quality issue: 3.2% defect rate in last shipment from [Supplier], part [PN]"
- "Request capacity increase from [Supplier] for Q3"

WHAT THE AGENT DOES:
- Pulls supplier contact data from SharePoint (Supplier Directory)
- Retrieves current open NCRs for that supplier
- Drafts an escalation email with the right tone and required fields
- Suggests next actions based on escalation level (L1/L2/L3)

ESCALATION LEVELS:
L1 (Supplier Quality Eng.): < 5% defect rate, single shipment
L2 (Supplier Mgmt. + Purchasing): Repeat issue, line impact <4h
L3 (VP Operations + Legal): Line stop, recall risk, contract breach

REQUIRED FIELDS IN EVERY ESCALATION:
- Supplier name + DUNS number
- Affected part number(s)
- Production impact (Yes/No, line, timing)
- Corrective action requested
- Response deadline
